Q1 : What is multitasking ?
Ans  : performing multiple task at one time is called multitasking.
       there are two types of multitasking : 
       1 : process based multitasking:
	       a program which is in a running state is called process.
           process based multitasking is executing several tasks simultaneously where each task is
		   a seperate independent process in called process based multitasking.
           for ex : process based  multitasking enables you to run the java IDE at the same time 
           while you are using a text editor or visiting a website using chrome.  		   
       2 : thread based multitasking:
	       is executing the several tasks simultaneously where each task is a seperate 
		   independent part of  the same program/process which is called thread.
	       a process(vlc) consist of multiple threads. so any process works with multiple 
           threads to accomplish its process to increase the performance and reduce the 
		   responsibility so this is thread based multitasking. 
		   
