Q5 : what is thread life cycle?
Ans :as we know thread is well known for independent execution during the life cycle a thread can 
     move from different states . 
     1 : new state (born)
     2 : runnable state (ready)
     3 : running state (execution)
     4 : waiting state (blocked/waiting)
     5 : dead state (exit)
	 
	 1 : new state - when ever a thread object is created it is always in new state.
	 2 : runnable state - when thread use start method it moves from new state to runnable state
	 3 : running state - when thread scheduler select the thread then thread moves into running 
                         state and execute the code.
     4 : waiting state - when ever a thread is inactive for short period of time.then the 
                         thread is in blocked state or waiting state. 
                         for eg : when the thread invoke(use) sleep method then thread moves into
						          waiting state/ blocked state.
 	 5 : dead state - when thread finish its job then it terminates normally.
	 

