Q8 : what is join method? 
Ans : the main purpose of join method is to put the other thread into waiting state.
      join method also throw the checked exception that is interrupted exception.
      If you use the join() method on Thread A, then Thread B will enter the waiting state. 
      While Thread B is waiting, Thread A will execute fully. Once Thread A completes, 
      Thread B will resume execution.
	  
