Q14 : what is thread priority?
Ans -  in java it is possible to assign the priority to a thread if we dont assign the priority
       to a thread than jvm will automatically asign a priorty 5 to a thread . 
       
     to set these priorities java thread class has provided two predifined methods : 
     1 : setPriority() - we can set the priority of thread. 
     2 : getPriority() - whatever priority we set we can get that priority.
 	 
	 the thread class has also provided three pre defined final static variable and its value lies
	 between 1 to 10 : 
     
     these are three predefined final static variable 
     Thread.MIN_PRIORITY = 1
	 Thread.NORM_PRIORITY = 5
     Thread.MAX_PRIORITY = 10	 
 	 
	 
	Note : max value priority will run first suppose there are two threads having priority 
	7 and 8  so thread having priority 8 will run first than thread having priority 7 will run 
	second.  
	
	And if we dont set the priority of thread than all the threads priorities will be set as 5
	by jvm .
	
	And if we give priority above the range suppose t1.setPriority(12) so it will throw the 
    exception which is illegal argument exception.

