Q17 : What is deadlock ? 
Ans: If two threads are waiting for each other forever such type of situation is called deadlock.
     
	 suppose Thread1 is holding object1 and Thread2 is holding Object2 now suppose Thread1 wants to get Object2
	 and similary Thread2 wants to get the Object1 but they both cant get each other object this situation is
	 called deadlock.
	 
	 synchronized keyword is the cause of deadlock hence whenever we are using synchronized keyword we have to 
	 take special care(means through synchronized keyword we are getting deadlock).
	 
	 If we remove atleast one synchronized keyword then we wont get deadlock.Hence synchronized keyword is the 
     only reason for deadlock due to this while using synchronized keyword we have to handel it carefully.
	 
	 
